      "rationale": "Numerical solver error as a distinct credibility factor applies primarily to custom or research solvers where iterative convergence tolerances and solver-specific numerical drift must be independently characterized. The commercial implicit solver (Ansys Mechanical) used in this study employs well-established sparse direct and iterative linear solvers with convergence criteria documented in the solver theory manual. Solver residual convergence is monitored automatically and all runs achieved force and displacement residuals below 1e-4. No evidence of solver-specific numerical error beyond what is captured under Numerical code verification (NAFEMS benchmarks) and Discretization error (GCI study). This factor is therefore not-applicable to the commercial implicit FEA context of this COU."
