    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/nagaraja-cou1-rva",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-applicable",
      "rationale": "The 'Relevance of the validation activities to the COU' factor is intended to assess whether validation experiments performed in a surrogate or analogous context can be extrapolated to the actual COU. In this package, the validation activity IS the COU — the FEA model is validated directly against ASTM F1717 bench tests of the identical non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct under the identical loading configuration. There is no gap between the validation context and the COU context requiring a relevance argument. This factor is therefore not-applicable: the validation and the COU are co-extensive, and no extrapolation across contexts is required."
